properties.name: Amazon Rainforest
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsAmazonasI think this would be the last stop on my world tour. Although it might be the most adventurous and dangerous. I would visit the Amazon Rainforest. This way I\'m getting closer to home but at the same time I\'m ending the vacation with a bang.

properties.name: Cairo, Egypt
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsCairo, EgyptAncient Egyptian culture has fascinated me since my first mummy horror movie.

properties.name: Home
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsRochester, NYThis is my home base, I\'ll start off my vacation from here

properties.name: Jerusalem, Israel
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsThere\'s so much religious history here. I feel that this would be one of the more profound stops on my world vacation.

properties.name: Kenya
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsKenyaMasai Mara is a park in Kenya that offers safari\'s. I would love to see the African Wildlife.

properties.name: London, England
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsLondon, EnglandI imagine this would be my first stop after college. Sort of a way to ease into travelling. Also, they speak English so I don\'t have to worry about translating.

properties.name: Paris
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsparisWhat trip around Europe would be complete without stopping at Paris?

properties.name: Pyramids of Giza, at Egypt
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsPyramids of GizaMore Egypt stuff that I want to check out.

properties.name: Rome, Italy
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsRome, ItalyOne of my history teachers claimed this is where Western Civilization began. I would love to check out the Colosseum.

properties.name: Zimbabwe
properties.description: Posted by MikenapsZimbabweIf you\'ve ever heard of the Elias fund, its a not for profit organization that attempts to strengthen Zimbabwe\'s youth through education. I\'d love to go teach for a year or two there. I think that\'d be an experience.
